    "body": "Fixes #39697\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nAfter closing and reopening Neovim, `]'` and `['` fail with `E92: Buffer 0 not found` when navigating to marks restored from ShaDa. Direct jumps like `'a` work correctly because the two motions use different code paths:\r\n\r\n- `'a` goes through `mark_get_local()`, which rewrites `fnum` to `buf->b_fnum` before returning, accidentally fixing the bad value.\r\n- `]'` uses `getnextmark()`, which scans `b_namedm[]` directly without fixing `fnum`, so it sees `fnum = 0` and fails.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nSet `.fnum = buf->b_fnum` when restoring local marks from ShaDa.\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
